|Abstract||Adversarial representations are a key component in deep neural networks. We propose a novel approach to achieve high-quality representations of adversarial attacks, which leads to robustness to adversarial attacks crafted to fool the full classifier. We demonstrate that intermediate layer predictions exhibit inherent robustness to adversarial attacks crafted to fool the full classifier, and propose a robust aggregation mechanism based on Vickrey auction that allows for the efficient aggregation of adversarial attacks. We also demonstrate that the adversarial attack is able to exploit the robustness of the intermediate layer predictions, which is important for the robustness of the adversarial representations.|
